{"bookId": "67656ccf18ff438b6c18cc4c","moduleId": "67656ccf18ff438b6c18cc4c","subjectId": "67656cd518ff438b6c18cc4d","chapterId": "67656cd518ff438b6c18cc52","subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","count": 13,"questions": [{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "If $\\mathrm{n}$ is the number density and $\\mathrm{d}$ is the diameter of the molecule, then the average distance covered by a molecule between two successive collisions (i.e. mean free path) is represented by :","options": ["$\\sqrt{2} \\mathrm{n} \\pi \\mathrm{d}^2$","$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2 n \\pi d^2}}$","$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2} n \\pi d^2}$","$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2} n^2 \\pi^2 d^2}$"],"answer": 2,"solution": "$\\mathrm{n}=$ number of molecule per unit volume\n$\\mathrm{d}=$ diameter of the molecule\n$\\lambda=\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2} \\pi \\mathrm{d}^2 \\mathrm{n}}$\n(By Theory)","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "6644671f970e6e9ab542d065","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 2)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "The temperature of a gas having <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>25</mn></msup></math> molecules per cubic meter at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>38</mn><mo> </mo><mi>atm</mi></math> (Given, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>38</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>23</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>)</mo></math> is :","options": ["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>500</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>300</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<p>From ideal gas equation, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>N</mi><msub><mi>N</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></mfrac><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo></math> total number of molecules</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>N</mi><mi>V</mi></mfrac><mfenced><mfrac><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>N</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></mfrac></mfenced><mi>T</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>N</mi><mi>V</mi></mfrac><mi>k</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>38</mn><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>25</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>38</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>23</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>≈</mo><mn>500</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math></p>","difficulty": "Easy","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "6682bd72ba0e94a3c4025cb4","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (29 Jan Shift 2)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "<p>Two thermodynamical process are shown in the figure. The molar heat capacity for process <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></math>. The molar heat capacity at constant pressure and constant volume are represented by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub></math>, respectively. Choose the correct statement.</p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4c085d90-f6f0-4a5e-b68e-ff6a65779362.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 256px;\"/>","options": ["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>∞</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub></math>"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4c085d90-f6f0-4a5e-b68e-ff6a65779362.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 256px;\"/></p><p>For process <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>log</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>γ</mi><mi>log</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>⇒</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>V</mi><mi>γ</mi></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>γ</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><msup><mi>V</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>γ</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo></math> Constant</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>γ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>…</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>Likewise, for process <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>P</mi><msup><mi>V</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo></math> Constant</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>v</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>v</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>…</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>Also, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>v</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>R</mi><mo> </mo><mo>…</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>By <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced></math>, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>v</mi></msub></math></p>","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "6682bd73ba0e94a3c4025cba","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "Given below are two statements :\nStatement (I) : The mean free path of gas molecules is inversely proportional to square of molecular diameter.\nStatement (II) : Average kinetic energy of gas molecules is directly proportional to absolute temperature of gas.\nIn the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below :","options": ["Statement I is true but Statement II is false","Both Statement I and Statement II are false","Both Statement I and Statement II are true","Statement I is false but Statement II is true"],"answer": 2,"solution": "$\\begin{aligned} & \\lambda=\\frac{\\mathrm{RT}}{\\sqrt{2} \\pi \\mathrm{d}^2 \\mathrm{~N}_{\\mathrm{A}} \\mathrm{P}} \\\\ & \\mathrm{KE}=\\frac{\\mathrm{f}}{2} \\mathrm{nRT}\\end{aligned}$","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "66446746970e6e9ab542d1d2","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 2)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "The specific heat at constant pressure of a real gas obeying $P V^2=R T$ equation is:","options": ["$\\frac{R}{3}+C_V$","$C_V+R$","$C_V+\\frac{R}{2 V}$","$R$"],"answer": 2,"solution": "$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{dQ}=\\mathrm{du}+\\mathrm{dW} \\\\\n& \\mathrm{CdT}=\\mathrm{C}_{\\mathrm{V}} \\mathrm{dT}+\\mathrm{PdV} \\\\\n& \\therefore \\mathrm{PV}^2=\\mathrm{RT} \\\\\n& \\mathrm{P}=\\text { constant } \\\\\n& \\mathrm{P}(2 \\mathrm{VdV})=\\mathrm{RdT} \\\\\n& \\mathrm{PdV}=\\frac{\\mathrm{RdT}}{2 \\mathrm{~V}} \\\\\n&\n\\end{aligned}$<br />Put in equation (1)\n$\\mathrm{C}=\\mathrm{C}_{\\mathrm{V}}+\\frac{\\mathrm{R}}{2 \\mathrm{~V}}$","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "6644672a970e6e9ab542d0cb","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (06 Apr Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "A block of ice at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> is slowly heated and converted to steam at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo> </mo><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>. Which of the following curves represent the phenomenon qualitatively:","options": ["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c786ae9c-14db-46a9-a091-c9170f550a04.png\" style=\"width: 220px; height: 185px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d632f854-f69c-4a66-8347-b0c637af15ef.png\" style=\"width: 220px; height: 178px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/617e7529-8a65-4e1b-9355-c802ef9b73c2.png\" style=\"width: 220px; height: 170px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/01688a02-4153-4031-b1d2-8d69786f8d65.png\" style=\"width: 220px; height: 182px;\"/>"],"answer": 3,"solution": "<blockquote><p>When the state of the substance is not changing, temperature of the substance increases when heat is supplied to it. But when the substance changes the state, the heat supplied to it used as latent heat and the temperature remains constant until all the substance converts to other state.</p><p>Therefore, temperature of ice first increases from  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo> </mo><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>. Then, remains constant at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> till whole ice is melted. Then, it increases from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo> </mo><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo> </mo><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>. Again it remains constant at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo> </mo><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> till whole water converts into steam.</p></blockquote>","difficulty": "Easy","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "6682bd70ba0e94a3c4025ca6","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 2)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "<p>Two conductors have the same resistances at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo> </mo><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> but their temperature coefficients of resistance are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>. The respective temperature coefficients for their series and parallel combinations are :</p>","options": ["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>"],"answer": 1,"solution": "<p>Change in resistance due to temperature is given by, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>R</mi><mo>'</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>For Series Combination:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>R</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mi>R</mi><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>For Parallel Combination:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>R</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced></mstyle></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced></mstyle></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mstyle></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mstyle></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>∆</mo><msup><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>Neglecting small terms</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>∆</mo><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>α</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "6682bd70ba0e94a3c4025ca7","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "P-T diagram of an ideal gas having three different densities $\\rho_1, \\rho_2, \\rho_3$ (in three different cases) is shown in the figure. Which of the following is correct :\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/FY3RknQd1DR5i3YKub5pOiXUSbj4Xn7hbwpUytlXyE8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","options": ["$\\rho_1>\\rho_2$","$\\rho_2 < \\rho_3$","$\\rho_1=\\rho_2=\\rho_3$","$\\rho_1 < \\rho_2$"],"answer": 0,"solution": "For ideal gas\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& P V=n R T \\\\\n& P V=\\frac{m}{M} R T \\\\\n& P=\\left(\\frac{M}{V}\\right) \\frac{R T}{M} \\\\\n& P=\\frac{\\rho R T}{M}\n\\end{aligned}$\n(Where $\\mathrm{m}$ is mass of gas and $\\mathrm{M}$ is molecular mass of gas)\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/sB72bMqLldNuXVQOFMuzIj48-a6mJ8Tb91CeUaR8zt0.original.fullsize.png\"><br />for same temperature $\\mathrm{P}_1>\\mathrm{P}_2>\\mathrm{P}_3$\nSo $\\rho_1>\\rho_2>\\rho_3$","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "66446702970e6e9ab542cf58","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (04 Apr Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "A sample of 1 mole gas at temperature $\\mathrm{T}$ is adiabatically expanded to double its volume. If adiabatic constant for the gas is $\\gamma=\\frac{3}{2}$, then the work done by the gas in the process is:","options": ["$\\frac{R}{T}[2-\\sqrt{2}]$","$\\frac{T}{R}[2+\\sqrt{2}]$","RT $[2-\\sqrt{2}]$","$\\mathrm{RT}[2+\\sqrt{2}]$"],"answer": 2,"solution": "$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{TV}^{\\gamma-1}=\\text { constant } \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{T}(\\mathrm{V})^{\\frac{3}{2}-1}=\\mathrm{T}_{\\mathrm{f}}(2 \\mathrm{~V})^{\\frac{3}{2}-1} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{TV}^{\\frac{1}{2}}=\\mathrm{T}_{\\mathrm{f}}(2)^{\\frac{1}{2}}(\\mathrm{~V})^{\\frac{1}{2}} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{T}_{\\mathrm{f}}=\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{T}}{\\sqrt{2}}\\right) \\\\ & \\text { Now, W.D. }=\\frac{\\mathrm{nR} \\Delta \\mathrm{T}}{1-\\gamma}=\\frac{1 \\cdot \\mathrm{R}\\left[\\frac{\\mathrm{T}}{\\sqrt{2}}-\\mathrm{T}\\right]}{1-\\frac{3}{2}} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\text { W.D. }=2 \\mathrm{RT}\\left[1-\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}}\\right] \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\text { W.D. }=\\mathrm{RT}[2-\\sqrt{2}]\\end{aligned}$","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "66446751970e6e9ab542d233","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "A real gas within a closed chamber at $27^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}$ undergoes the cyclic process as shown in figure. The gas obeys $P V^3=R T$ equation for the path $A$ to $B$. The net work done in the complete cycle is (assuming $R=8 \\mathrm{~J} / \\mathrm{mol} \\mathrm{K}$ ):\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/MaShLXI7MYXTuG2HJc9_KIJxN1dVYeOQKqX0uLnKwWc.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","options": ["$20 \\mathrm{~J}$","$205 \\mathrm{~J}$","$-20 \\mathrm{~J}$","$225 \\mathrm{~J}$"],"answer": 1,"solution": "$\\mathrm{W}_{\\mathrm{AB}}=\\int \\mathrm{PdV} \\quad$ (Assuming $\\mathrm{T}$ to be constant)\n$\\begin{aligned} & =\\int \\frac{\\mathrm{RTdV}}{\\mathrm{V}^3} \\\\ & =\\mathrm{RT} \\int_2^4 \\mathrm{~V}^{-3} \\mathrm{dV} \\\\ & =8 \\times 300 \\times\\left(-\\frac{1}{2}\\left[\\frac{1}{4^2}-\\frac{1}{2^2}\\right]\\right) \\\\ & =225 \\mathrm{~J}\\end{aligned}$\n$\\begin{aligned}& \\mathrm{W}_{\\mathrm{BC}}=\\mathrm{P} \\int_4^2 \\mathrm{dV}=10(2-4)=-20 \\mathrm{~J} \\\\& \\mathrm{~W}_{\\mathrm{CA}}=0 \\\\& \\therefore \\mathrm{W}_{\\text {cycle }}=205 \\mathrm{~J}\n\\end{aligned}$","difficulty": "Hard","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "6644675b970e6e9ab542d28e","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 2)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "<p>A thermodynamic system is taken from an original state <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> to an intermediate state <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> by a linear process as shown in the figure. Its volume is then reduced to the original value from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math> by an isobaric process. The total work done by the gas from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math> would be :</p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2a96272b-4254-4cee-84b3-193b8206f736.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 222px;\"/>","options": ["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>33800</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2200</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>600</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>800</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>"],"answer": 3,"solution": "<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2a96272b-4254-4cee-84b3-193b8206f736.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 222px;\"/></p><p>Work done during the path <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> can be written as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>W</mi><mi>AB</mi></msub></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>(</mo><mn>8000</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4000</mn><mo>)</mo><mo> </mo><mi>dyne</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>dyne</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>7</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>2400</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>The work done during the process <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>W</mi><mi>BC</mi></msub></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfenced><mrow><mn>4000</mn><mo> </mo><mi>dyne</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>dyne</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1600</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Hence, the total work done is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>W</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><msub><mi>W</mi><mi>AB</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mi>BC</mi></msub></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>2400</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1600</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>800</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p>","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "6682bd71ba0e94a3c4025caa","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (29 Jan Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "During an adiabatic process, the pressure of a gas is found to be proportional to the cube of its absolute temperature. The ratio of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>v</mi></msub></mfrac></math> for the gas is :","options": ["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer": 1,"solution": "<p>It is given that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>∝</mo><msup><mi>T</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>P</mi><msup><mi>T</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mtext>constant</mtext><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>For an adiabatic process,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><msup><mi>V</mi><mi>γ</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mtext>constant</mtext><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Assuming the gas to be a perfect gas, it can be written from equation (2) that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>P</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mi>γ</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mtext>constant</mtext><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mi>P</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>γ</mi></mrow></msup><msup><mi>T</mi><mi>γ</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mtext>constant</mtext><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>P</mi><msup><mi>T</mi><mfrac><mi>γ</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>γ</mi></mrow></mfrac></msup><mo>=</mo><mtext>constant</mtext></math></p><p>By comparing with equation(1), we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mi>γ</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>γ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>γ</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>γ</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>γ</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>γ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>","difficulty": "Easy","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "6682bd71ba0e94a3c4025cab","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (27 Jan Shift 2)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","q": "<p>The given figure represents two isobaric processes for the same mass of an ideal gas, then</p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/05dc0f9f-f20a-49af-8454-c5508d494c0a.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 200px;\"/>","options": ["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>≥</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>"],"answer": 3,"solution": "<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/05dc0f9f-f20a-49af-8454-c5508d494c0a.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 200px;\"/></p><p>As we know, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>P</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mi>T</mi></math></p><p>Therefore, slope <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>P</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>Or slope <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∝</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>P</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>As <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mfenced><mi>Slope</mi></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mfenced><mi>Slope</mi></mfenced><mn>1</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></p>","difficulty": "Easy","source": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024","_marksId": "6682bd71ba0e94a3c4025cad","paperSource": "JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 1)"}]}